                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18121202-54-off314 t18121202-54-crimeloc318"></join>. I lost my pots out of the tap room on the 2nd of November. I had information that he had them in his trowsers. I let him go out, and then I asked him what he had got; he said, nothing. I took a pint pot out of his trowsers, and a pint pot out of his pocket. These are the pots; they are mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was in liquor. I laid my head on the table; somebody in the room put a pint pot in my pocket, and placed another between my legs.</p>
